snippet.textDisplay:
Because of the Corona virus thousands of performing artists are now losing the maturity, if not all of their gigs due to the venues having to shut down. Many of them might even be losing more than half a year‘s salary of unpaid rehearsals and hours of administration for these gigs. A cultural crisis is coming up along with the Corona virus, which is threatening the existence of numerous artforms.
So here‘s my suggestion: Why not bring together performing artists from all possible fields (music, dance, theatre, stand-up,...) and reinvest the money into a special production that all of them can be involved in creating and performing and then give them your amazing plattform to share it with the world?
Not only could you help those individuals get through those tough times financially, but also raise the awareness of the arts (and especially the people that are creating the art) being amongst the first to become extinct, should the situation get even worse.
After all, creativity and artistry are some of the most prescious traits of being human and they have the ability to bring us together and give us hope during these times.
